org.apache.flex.compiler.definitions

Interface IStyleDefinition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IDefinition, IDocumentableDefinition, IMetadataDefinition
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    StyleDefinition

    public interface IStyleDefinition
extends IMetadataDefinition
    Represents style metadata decorating a class definition, such as Style(name="color", type="uint", format="color", inherit="yes")].

    Use IDefinition.getBaseName()() to get the style's name (e.g., "color".

      • getNode

        IStyleTagNode getNode()
        Returns the IStyleTagNode from which this definition was created, if the definition came from the AST for a source file.

        This method may require the AST to be reloaded or regenerated and therefore may be slow.

        Specified by:
        getNode in interface IDefinition

      • getArrayType

        String getArrayType()
        Gets the value of this style's arrayType attribute.

        When the type attribute is "Array, the arrayType attribute specifies the type of the array elements.

        Returns:
        The value of the arrayType attribute as a String, or null.

      • resolveArrayType

        ITypeDefinition resolveArrayType(ICompilerProject project)
        Resolves the type specified by the arrayType attribute to a class or interface definitions.

        When the value of the type attribute is "Array", the arrayType attribute specifies the type of the array elements.

        Parameters:
        project - The ICompilerProject within which references should be resolved.
        Returns:
        An ITypeDefinition for the resolved array type, or null.

      • getEnumeration

        String[] getEnumeration()
        Gets the possible values of this style, as specified by its enumeration attribute.

        When the value of the type attribute is "String", the enumeration attribute specifies the allowed String values.

        Returns:
        The comma-separated values in the enumeration attribute as an array of Strings, or an empty array.
